            "id": "devotion",
            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EJehoshaphat%20received%20a%20bad%20report!%20A%20negative%20report%20can%20knock%20you%20down%2C%20as%20illustrated%20through%20the%20bad%20report%20given%20by%20the%20ten%20spies%20in%20Moses'%20day.%20Your%20response%20to%20a%20bad%20report%20is%20critical%2C%20as%20it%20often%20determines%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20situation.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EJehoshaphat's%20response%20teaches%20several%20lessons.%20First%2C%20don't%20respond%20in%20fear%2C%20but%20in%20faith%20(2%20Chronicles%2020%3A3).%20Second%2C%20find%20a%20promise%20that%20fits%20your%20case%20and%20stand%20upon%20that%20promise%2C%20using%20it%20as%20the%20basis%20of%20your%20prayer%20(v.%209).%20Third%2C%20based%20upon%20that%20same%20promise%2C%20claim%20your%20inheritance%20and%20stand%20your%20ground%2C%20resisting%20all%20%22claim%20jumpers%22%20(v.%2011).%20Fourth%2C%20turn%20the%20battle%20over%20to%20God%20(v.%2015).%20Finally%2C%20praise%20God%20for%20the%20victory%20in%20advance%20(vv.%2021-22).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20world%20views%20a%20bad%20report%20as%20the%20definitive%20statement%20of%20fact%20regarding%20a%20matter.%20As%20a%20Christian%2C%20however%2C%20you%20know%20that%20you%20can%20reverse%20an%20evil%20report.%20Jehoshaphat's%20ordeal%20was%20transformed%20from%20the%20dreadful%20fear%20and%20alarm%20of%20the%20first%20report%20to%20the%20joyful%2C%20triumphal%20return%20to%20Jerusalem.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EThe%20same%20battle%20plan%20that%20Jehoshaphat%20used%20will%20work%20for%20you.%20Fear%20not%2C%20find%20a%20promise%2C%20claim%20your%20inheritance%2C%20turn%20the%20battle%20over%20to%20God%2C%20and%20praise%20Him%20in%20advance.%20You%20will%20surely%20win!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "2Chr.19:1-20:37",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E2%20Chronicles%2019%3A1-20%3A37%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EJehoshaphat%20Appoints%20Judges%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20King%20Jehoshaphat%20of%20Judah%20arrived%20safely%20home%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EJehu%20son%20of%20Hanani%20the%20seer%20went%20out%20to%20meet%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20should%20you%20help%20the%20wicked%20and%20love%20those%20who%20hate%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20he%20asked%20the%20king.%20%26%23x201C%3BBecause%20of%20what%20you%20have%20done%2C%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20very%20angry%20with%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EEven%20so%2C%20there%20is%20some%20good%20in%20you%2C%20for%20you%20have%20removed%20the%20Asherah%20poles%20throughout%20the%20land%2C%20and%20you%20have%20committed%20yourself%20to%20seeking%20God.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoshaphat%20lived%20in%20Jerusalem%2C%20but%20he%20went%20out%20among%20the%20people%2C%20traveling%20from%20Beersheba%20to%20the%20hill%20country%20of%20Ephraim%2C%20encouraging%20the%20people%20to%20return%20to%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20the%20God%20of%20their%20ancestors.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20appointed%20judges%20throughout%20the%20nation%20in%20all%20the%20fortified%20towns%2C%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3Eand%20he%20said%20to%20them%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BAlways%20think%20carefully%20before%20pronouncing%20judgment.%20Remember%20that%20you%20do%20not%20judge%20to%20please%20people%20but%20to%20please%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20He%20will%20be%20with%20you%20when%20you%20render%20the%20verdict%20in%20each%20case.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EFear%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20judge%20with%20integrity%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20our%20God%20does%20not%20tolerate%20perverted%20justice%2C%20partiality%2C%20or%20the%20taking%20of%20bribes.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EIn%20Jerusalem%2C%20Jehoshaphat%20appointed%20some%20of%20the%20Levites%20and%20priests%20and%20clan%20leaders%20in%20Israel%20to%20serve%20as%20judges%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E19%3A8%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%3B%20the%20meaning%20of%20the%20Hebrew%20is%20uncertain.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20cases%20involving%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20regulations%20and%20for%20civil%20disputes.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThese%20were%20his%20instructions%20to%20them%3A%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20must%20always%20act%20in%20the%20fear%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20with%20faithfulness%20and%20an%20undivided%20heart.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EWhenever%20a%20case%20comes%20to%20you%20from%20fellow%20citizens%20in%20an%20outlying%20town%2C%20whether%20a%20murder%20case%20or%20some%20other%20violation%20of%20God%26%23x2019%3Bs%20laws%2C%20commands%2C%20decrees%2C%20or%20regulations%2C%20you%20must%20warn%20them%20not%20to%20sin%20against%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20so%20that%20he%20will%20not%20be%20angry%20with%20you%20and%20them.%20Do%20this%20and%20you%20will%20not%20be%20guilty.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_19_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2219%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAmariah%20the%20high%20priest%20will%20have%20final%20say%20in%20all%20cases%20involving%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20Zebadiah%20son%20of%20Ishmael%2C%20a%20leader%20from%20the%20tribe%20of%20Judah%2C%20will%20have%20final%20say%20in%20all%20civil%20cases.%20The%20Levites%20will%20assist%20you%20in%20making%20sure%20that%20justice%20is%20served.%20Take%20courage%20as%20you%20fulfill%20your%20duties%2C%20and%20may%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20be%20with%20those%20who%20do%20what%20is%20right.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_1%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E2%20Chronicles%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EWar%20with%20Surrounding%20Nations%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20this%2C%20the%20armies%20of%20the%20Moabites%2C%20Ammonites%2C%20and%20some%20of%20the%20Meunites%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20some%20Greek%20manuscripts%20(see%20also%2026%3A7)%3B%20Hebrew%20repeats%20%3Cem%3EAmmonites.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20declared%20war%20on%20Jehoshaphat.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_2%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EMessengers%20came%20and%20told%20Jehoshaphat%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BA%20vast%20army%20from%20Edom%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A2a%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20one%20Hebrew%20manuscript%3B%20most%20Hebrew%20manuscripts%20and%20ancient%20versions%20read%20%3Cem%3EAram.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20marching%20against%20you%20from%20beyond%20the%20Dead%20Sea.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A2b%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Hebrew%20%3Cem%3Ethe%20sea.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20They%20are%20already%20at%20Hazazon-tamar.%26%23x201D%3B%20(This%20was%20another%20name%20for%20En-gedi.)%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_3%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoshaphat%20was%20terrified%20by%20this%20news%20and%20begged%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20for%20guidance.%20He%20also%20ordered%20everyone%20in%20Judah%20to%20begin%20fasting.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_4%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20people%20from%20all%20the%20towns%20of%20Judah%20came%20to%20Jerusalem%20to%20seek%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20help.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_5%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EJehoshaphat%20stood%20before%20the%20community%20of%20Judah%20and%20Jerusalem%20in%20front%20of%20the%20new%20courtyard%20at%20the%20Temple%20of%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_6%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20prayed%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BO%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%2C%20God%20of%20our%20ancestors%2C%20you%20alone%20are%20the%20God%20who%20is%20in%20heaven.%20You%20are%20ruler%20of%20all%20the%20kingdoms%20of%20the%20earth.%20You%20are%20powerful%20and%20mighty%3B%20no%20one%20can%20stand%20against%20you!%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_7%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3EO%26%23xA0%3Bour%20God%2C%20did%20you%20not%20drive%20out%20those%20who%20lived%20in%20this%20land%20when%20your%20people%20Israel%20arrived%3F%20And%20did%20you%20not%20give%20this%20land%20forever%20to%20the%20descendants%20of%20your%20friend%20Abraham%3F%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_8%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EYour%20people%20settled%20here%20and%20built%20this%20Temple%20to%20honor%20your%20name.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_9%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThey%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BWhenever%20we%20are%20faced%20with%20any%20calamity%20such%20as%20war%2C%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E20%3A9%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Or%20%3Cem%3Esword%20of%20judgment%3B%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20%3Cem%3Esword%2C%20judgment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20plague%2C%20or%20famine%2C%20we%20can%20come%20to%20stand%20in%20your%20presence%20before%20this%20Temple%20where%20your%20name%20is%20honored.%20We%20can%20cry%20out%20to%20you%20to%20save%20us%2C%20and%20you%20will%20hear%20us%20and%20rescue%20us.%26%23x2019%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_10%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BAnd%20now%20see%20what%20the%20armies%20of%20Ammon%2C%20Moab%2C%20and%20Mount%20Seir%20are%20doing.%20You%20would%20not%20let%20our%20ancestors%20invade%20those%20nations%20when%20Israel%20left%20Egypt%2C%20so%20they%20went%20around%20them%20and%20did%20not%20destroy%20them.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_11%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20see%20how%20they%20reward%20us!%20For%20they%20have%20come%20to%20throw%20us%20out%20of%20your%20land%2C%20which%20you%20gave%20us%20as%20an%20inheritance.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20_12%22%20bk%3D%22chr2%22%20ch%3D%2220%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3EO%26%23xA0%3Bour%20God%2C%20won%26%23x2019%3Bt%20you%20stop%20them%3F%20We%20are%20powerless%20against%20this%20mighty%20army%20that%20is%20about%20to%20attack%20us.%20We%20do%20not%20know%20what%20to%20do%2C%20but%20we%20are%20looking%20to%20you%20for%20help.%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22chr2_20